# eVisit UI — AI Coding Rules
# Last synced with CLAUDE.md: 2026-03-25
# If CLAUDE.md has changed, regenerate from docs/ai/

## Technology Constraints (DO NOT use newer versions)

- React 17 (NOT 18 — no createRoot, useId, automatic batching)
- MUI v5 (NOT v6)
- styled-components v5 (NOT v6)
- MSW v1 (NOT v2 — handler format: `rest.get(url, (req, res, ctx) => ...)`)
- React Router 6
- TypeScript 5.9+ (strict mode)
- Node.js >= 22

## Restricted Imports (ENFORCED BY ESLINT)

| DO NOT import from | INSTEAD use |
|---|---|
| `@testing-library/react` (render) | `ev-test/test-utils` |
| `react-redux` (useDispatch, useSelector) | `ev-store/redux` (useAppDispatch, useAppSelector) |
| `react-i18next` (useTranslation, Trans) | `ev-i18n` |
| `react-router-dom` (useNavigate) | `ev-hooks/navigate` (useAppNavigate) |
| `styled-components` | `styled-components/macro` |
| `@mui/material` (barrel import) | Individual imports (`@mui/material/Grid`) |
| `@mui/material/Typography` | `ev-components/Text` |
| `btoa` / `atob` | `ev-utils/base64` |

## Component Preferences

ALWAYS use ev-components wrappers instead of raw MUI or HTML:

- Button → `ev-components/Button`
- Input/TextField → `ev-components/Input`
- Dialog/Modal → `ev-components/Dialog`
- Select → `ev-components/Dropdown`
- Typography → `ev-components/Text`
- Tabs → `ev-components/Tabs`
- Snackbar → `ev-components/Snackbar` or `useToast()` from `ev-hooks/toast`

See `docs/ai/component-catalog.md` for the full catalog of 47+ reusable components.
See `docs/ai/decision-trees/component-selection.md` for "use existing vs create new" guidance.

## Design Tokens (MANDATORY)

NEVER use raw hex/rgb colors. ALWAYS use EVColors:

```tsx
import { EVColors, Elevations } from 'ev-theme/styles';

// Colors: EVColors.text.default, EVColors.surface.background, EVColors.border.default, etc.
// Shadows: Elevations.elevation0 through elevation8
// Typography: Text.Body, Text.Description, Text.Headline3, etc.
// Breakpoints: useLayout() hook from ev-hooks/layout (NOT CSS media queries)
```

See `docs/ai/design-tokens.md` for the complete token reference.

## Code Style

- Arrow function components (NEVER `function` keyword or `React.FC`)
- `const` by default (prefer-const)
- `===` always (no `==`)
- No `console.log` (only `console.warn`, `console.error`)
- No `any` type (use `unknown` with type guards)
- Max cyclomatic complexity: 15
- All user-visible strings wrapped in `t()` from `useTranslation()`
- `data-testid` on all interactive elements
- Imports from `src/` baseUrl (e.g., `import api from 'ev-api/api'`)

## Import Order (automated by Prettier)

1. External libraries (react, lodash)
2. @fullcalendar/*
3. @mui/*
4. @fortawesome/*
5. ev-* packages (bare, e.g., `ev-store`)
6. ev-* deep imports (e.g., `ev-store/redux`)
7. app-* imports
8. Relative imports (./, ../)

## JSX Conventions

- Sort props alphabetically, shorthand last: `<Button disabled id="x" label="Y" open />`
- No curly braces for string props: `<Button id="x" />` not `<Button id={"x"} />`
- Boolean shorthand: `<Dialog open />` not `<Dialog open={true} />`

## Responsive Design

Use `useLayout()` from `ev-hooks/layout` for all responsive behavior:

```tsx
const { isMobile, isTablet, isDesktop } = useLayout();
```

Breakpoints: mobile (< 744px), tablet (744-1024px), desktop (> 1024px)
Pass layout flags as transient props: `$isMobile` (with $ prefix)

## Testing

- Use `test()` not `it()`
- Use `render` from `ev-test/test-utils` (wraps with providers)
- Use MSW v1 handlers from `ev-test/request-handlers/`
- Use fishery factories from `ev-test/test-mocks/api-response/`
- Include `validateAccessibility(container)` for a11y testing
- Test at both `mobile` and `desktop` layouts for responsive components

## i18n

- ALL user-visible strings must be wrapped in `t()` from `useTranslation()`
- Use `nt()` for strings in non-component contexts (tests, stories)
- Import from `ev-i18n` (NOT `react-i18next`)
- Flat key format (no nesting)

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

- Semantic HTML elements (button, a, ul/ol, table)
- All form inputs need label/ariaLabel/labelledBy
- `aria-live` for dynamic content updates
- Focus management for modals, drawers, route changes
- Visible focus indicators (never remove :focus-visible)
- 44x44px minimum touch targets on mobile
- Color + text/icon for all status indicators (not color alone)
- Contrast: 4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for large text and UI components

## Commit Convention

```
CU-<taskId>: <Short description>
```

Branch naming: `CU-<taskId>_<description-with-dashes>`

## File Naming

- PascalCase for components: `Button.tsx`, `Dialog.tsx`
- kebab-case for utilities/hooks: `date-time.ts`, `navigate.tsx`
- kebab-case for Redux slices: `selected-visit.ts`
- Tests: `*.test.tsx` in `__tests__/` directories
- Stories: `*.stories.tsx` co-located with component
